   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>OUTLINE TWO PROPHESYING</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>IN THE CHURCH MEETINGS</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>FOR THE ORGANIC BUILDING UP</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>OF THE CHURCH AS THE BODY OF CHRIST Scripture Reading: Luke 10:1-6; Rom 15:16; 1 Pet 2:5; John 21:15; 1 Thes 2:7; Eph 4:11-12; Heb 10:24-25; 1 Cor 14:3-5, 26 The organic way to practice the Lord s present recovery for the organic building up of the Body of Christ: The organic preaching of the gospel saving sinners by contacting them where they are: God s pattern in the Old Testament: Coming to find and visit fallen man Gen 3:8-9 , preaching the gospel to fallen man 3:15 , and ministering salvation to the condemned man 3:21 .</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Coming down to visit Israel to deliver them out of the tyranny of Pharaoh in Egypt Exo 3:8.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The example of the Lord Jesus: Coming down from heaven to save sinners 1 Tim 1:15.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Visiting Zaccheus with His dynamic salvation Luke 19:1-10.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Visiting the Samaritan woman to bring her the living water John 4:3-15.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Journeying from city to city and village to village with the twelve to proclaim and bring the good news of the kingdom of God Luke 8:1.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The Lord s sending the disciples: Sending the twelve to go to the cities and villages to visit the lost sheep of the house of Israel and bring them peace Matt 10:5-8, 11-13 .</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Sending the seventy to go to every city and place to seek the sons of peace Luke 10:1-6 .</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Charging His disciples to go into all the world and preach the gospel to all the creation Mark 16:15 .</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Charging His disciples to go and disciple all the nations by baptizing them into the Triune God Matt 28:19 .</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Going out to visit people being the most effective way to preach the gospel.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The meaning of the organic preaching of the gospel: To impart Christ into the repentant and believing sinners Gal 1:16 .</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>To minister Christ in His riches to people Eph 3:8 .</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>To beget sinners as children of God that they may become the members of the organic Body of Christ 1 Cor 4:15; Rom 12:5.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>To baptize the believing sinners into the Triune God Matt 28:19.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>To bear fruit as an issue of the genuine enjoyment of Christ John 15:5, 16a.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The organic labor of preaching the gospel: Making the New Testament priesthood of the gospel a part of our daily life by saving sinners and offering them to God as spiritual sacrifices Rom 15:16; 1 Pet 2:5.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Laboring in the gospel habitually, regularly, and constantly 2 Tim 4:2; 1 Cor 9:22-23.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The organic nourishing and cherishing of the new believers in their homes: Meeting with them regularly in their homes until they become established in the faith Acts 5:42.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Feeding them as the Lord s lambs John 21:15: Bringing them into the practice of exercising their spirit and calling on the Lord Eph 6:18a; Rom 10:12b.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Teaching them the basic truths of God s redemption.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Being a nursing mother to nourish and cherish them 1 Thes 2:7: Taking care of their spiritual need and their need in practical affairs, sicknesses, and afflictions.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Praying for them.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Bringing them up and leading them to present themselves to God as living sacrifices Rom 12:1.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>The organic perfecting of the saints in the small group meetings: Participating in the fellowship, interceding, and mutual care with the saints Acts 2:42, 46; 12:5, 12.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Inciting one another to love and good works, exhorting one another Heb 10:24-25.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Learning and teaching the truth and the experience of life mutually Acts 2:42.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Preaching the gospel Acts 5:42; 2:46-47.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Entreating and consoling the believers as a father 1 Thes 2:11; Acts 20:20, 31.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>Leading the believers to grow into Christ, the Head, in all things, to a full-grown man, unto the work of ministry the organic work for the building up of the Body of Christ Eph 4:11-16; Col 1:28-29.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>Carrying out the practical church life.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>The organic prophesying in the larger meetings of mutuality for the building up of the church as the organic Body of Christ: All prophesying mutually 1 Cor 14:24, 26.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>Speaking building up, encouragement, and consolation 1 Cor 14:3.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Convicting and judging people, exposing the secrets of people s hearts 1 Cor 14:24-25.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>The characteristics of the church meetings of mutuality according to the God-ordained way of each one has 1 Cor 14:26 : A one another meeting, a round-table meeting: 1 Speaking to one another Eph 5:19.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>2 Teaching and admonishing one another Col 3:16.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>3 Considering one another and exhorting one another Heb 10:24-25.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>4 Listening to one another 1 Thes 5:20.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>Making the believers living.</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>Developing the organic ability and function of the living members of Christ Eph 4:16.</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>Fitting the living believers taste.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>Renouncing the customs of the nations 2 Kings 17:8 NASB .</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>Building up the church as the organic Body of Christ 1 Cor 14:4-5, 26.</S>
   </TEXT>
